<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-10-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-10-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="665" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/411: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-15T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 15,
                                        1926—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>231. Your telegrams 462, October 8, 8 p.m. and 477, October 14, Noon.
                            Department considered that its instructions No. 217, October 5, 7 p.m.
                            sufficiently covered the matter to enable you to join your colleagues in
                            protest outlined in paragraph 3 of your urgent telegram 462, October 8,
                            8 p.m. No objection to wording of protest as amended is perceived by
                            Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>